                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d245">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">438.00/367: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Russell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-01-30T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 30, 1926—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 1—9:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. Department’s 6, January 26, 7 p.m. Minister for Foreign Affairs has verbally
                    informed me that he accepts suggested observations and explanations. At my
                    [suggestion he is] informing Haitian Minister at Washington accordingly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
